---
// Sous Clip landing page
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Sous Clip — Your recipes. Your server. Forever.</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Self-hosted recipe extractor for cooking videos. Paste a YouTube Short, Instagram Reel, or TikTok — get a clean recipe on your own server." />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500;700&family=Playfair+Display:wght@700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #FDFAF5;
      --surface: #F5F0E8;
      --border: #E2D9CC;
      --text: #1C1917;
      --muted: #78716C;
      --accent: #C2410C;
      --accent-alt: #15803D;
      --dark-bg: #1C1917;
      --dark-surface: #292524;
    }
    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
    body { font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; color: var(--text); background: var(--bg); }
    .display { font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; }
    .mono { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }
    .container { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }
    a { transition: opacity 0.15s; }
    a:hover { opacity: 0.85; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section style="padding: 80px 0 60px;">
    <div class="container" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 60px; align-items: center;">
      <div>
        <h1 class="display" style="font-size: 3.5rem; line-height: 1.1;">
          Rescue recipes<br/>from the feed.
        </h1>
        <p style="margin-top: 20px; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6;">
          Sous Clip turns any YouTube Short, Instagram Reel, or TikTok
          into a clean saved recipe — on your own server, in under 30 seconds.
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 32px; display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
          <a href="#quickstart" style="background: var(--accent); color: white; padding: 12px 24px; border-radius: 8px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem;">
            Deploy with Docker
          </a>
          <a href="https://github.com/yourname/Sous Clip" style="border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 12px 24px; border-radius: 8px; text-decoration: none; color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; font-size: 0.9rem;">
            View on GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 24px; display: flex; gap: 20px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); flex-wrap: wrap;">
          <span>Open source, MIT licensed</span>
          <span>Your data, your server</span>
          <span>Bring your own AI key</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-visual" style="background: var(--surface); border-radius: 16px; height: 360px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
        <span style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.9rem;">[ Demo video / animation placeholder ]</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Problem -->
  <section style="padding: 60px 0;">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 640px; text-align: center;">
      <p style="font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text);">
        You're scrolling. A recipe catches your eye — someone's making a garlic
        butter pasta that looks incredible. They rattle off the ingredients, the
        technique, the timing. You fumble for Notes. By the time you've paused
        the video, you've already lost half of it.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: 20px; font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); font-weight: 500;">
        You screenshot. You bookmark. You forget.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: 20px; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7;">
        Every recipe app out there will happily save it for you — on their server,
        behind their paywall, until they shut down.
        There had to be a better way.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works -->
  <section style="padding: 60px 0; background: var(--surface);">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="display" style="text-align: center; font-size: 2rem;">How it works</h2>
      <div class="steps-grid" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 40px; margin-top: 40px;">
        <div style="text-align: center;">
          <div style="font-size: 2rem; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700;">1</div>
          <h3 style="margin-top: 8px; font-weight: 700;">Paste or share the URL</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--muted);">Drop a link or use the mobile share sheet directly from Instagram, YouTube, or TikTok.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align: center;">
          <div style="font-size: 2rem; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700;">2</div>
          <h3 style="margin-top: 8px; font-weight: 700;">We handle the rest</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--muted);">The video is downloaded, the audio transcribed locally with Whisper, and your chosen AI extracts the structured recipe.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align: center;">
          <div style="font-size: 2rem; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700;">3</div>
          <h3 style="margin-top: 8px; font-weight: 700;">Yours forever</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--muted);">A clean recipe card — ingredients, steps, cook time, servings — saved to your library on your own server.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Features -->
  <section style="padding: 60px 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="features-grid" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px;">
        <div style="background: var(--surface); padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
          <h3 style="font-weight: 700;">Any short-form video</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">YouTube Shorts, Instagram Reels, TikTok — all supported via yt-dlp</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background: var(--surface); padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
          <h3 style="font-weight: 700;">Local transcription</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Whisper runs on your server with GPU or CPU — auto-detected, zero config</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background: var(--surface); padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
          <h3 style="font-weight: 700;">Your AI, your key</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Use Claude, OpenAI, or a local Ollama model. You're always in control</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background: var(--surface); padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
          <h3 style="font-weight: 700;">Mobile share sheet</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Install as a PWA and share videos directly from any app on your phone</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background: var(--surface); padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
          <h3 style="font-weight: 700;">Personal recipe library</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Search, tag, and browse every recipe you've ever saved</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background: var(--surface); padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
          <h3 style="font-weight: 700;">Self-hosted forever</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">SQLite database, single Docker command, your data never leaves your server</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pipeline Demo -->
  <section style="padding: 60px 0; background: var(--dark-bg); color: white;">
    <div class="container" style="text-align: center;">
      <h2 class="display" style="font-size: 2rem;">See it in action</h2>
      <div style="margin-top: 40px; display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center;">
        <div style="background: var(--dark-surface); padding: 16px 24px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Downloading video
        </div>
        <div style="color: var(--muted);">&rarr;</div>
        <div style="background: var(--dark-surface); padding: 16px 24px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Transcribing audio
        </div>
        <div style="color: var(--muted);">&rarr;</div>
        <div style="background: var(--dark-surface); padding: 16px 24px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Extracting recipe
        </div>
        <div style="color: var(--muted);">&rarr;</div>
        <div style="background: var(--accent); padding: 16px 24px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600;">
          Saved
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Self-Hosting / Quick Start -->
  <section id="quickstart" style="padding: 60px 0;">
    <div class="container quickstart-grid" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 60px; align-items: center;">
      <div>
        <h2 class="display" style="font-size: 2rem;">Built for people who believe their data is theirs.</h2>
        <p style="margin-top: 16px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7;">
          Sous Clip stores everything in a single SQLite file on your server.
          No cloud accounts. No usage limits. No vendor lock-in.
          Works behind Nginx Proxy Manager, Caddy, or Traefik.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div style="background: var(--dark-bg); padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; color: #e5e5e5; overflow-x: auto;">
        <pre class="mono" style="font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;"><code>git clone https://github.com/yourname/Sous Clip
cd Sous Clip
cp .env.example .env
docker compose up -d</code></pre>
        <p style="margin-top: 12px; color: var(--accent); font-size: 0.85rem;">&rarr; Open http://localhost:3000</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer style="padding: 40px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); text-align: center;">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="display" style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700;">Sous Clip</p>
      <p style="margin-top: 4px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); font-style: italic;">
        Your recipes. Your server. Forever.
      </p>
      <div style="margin-top: 16px; display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 20px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="https://github.com/yourname/Sous Clip" style="color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none;">GitHub</a>
        <a href="#" style="color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none;">Docs</a>
        <a href="https://reddit.com/r/selfhosted" style="color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none;">r/selfhosted</a>
        <a href="#" style="color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none;">License</a>
      </div>
      <p style="margin-top: 20px; font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--muted);">
        Built with care and a lot of cooking videos.
      </p>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <!-- Mobile responsive styles -->
  <style>
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      section:first-of-type { padding: 48px 0 40px !important; }
      section:first-of-type .container {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
        gap: 32px !important;
      }
      section:first-of-type h1 { font-size: 2.5rem !important; }
      .hero-visual { height: 200px !important; }
      .steps-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; gap: 24px !important; }
      .features-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; }
      .quickstart-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
        gap: 32px !important;
      }
    }
  </style>

</body>
</html>
